Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to
peel). Pop the potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim
the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}.
Halve the @premium tomato mix{190%g}, then pop them into a large #bowl{} with a
drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Pop half the beans into a medium #saucepan{} and roughly mash with a #potato masher{}.
Stir in the remaining beans, half the @chipotle paste{40%g} (add less if you don't
like heat), half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}, half the garlic and the
@water for the beans{75%ml}. Pop the saucepan on medium-high heat and bring to
the boil. Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
When hot, add the @British beef mince{360%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, remaining chipotle paste, chicken stock paste
and garlic.

Stir in the @water for the beef{150%ml} and @sugar for the sauce{1/2%tsp}, then
bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}. Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a baking tray
and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once ready, stir the roasted
potatoes through the mince.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Just before serving, add half the baby gem to the bowl with the tomatoes. Toss
to coat. To serve, top each tortilla with the remaining baby gem, spoonfuls of
beef mix, a sprinkle of cheese and a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}. Serve the
tacos (3 per person) with the refried beans and salad alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!